TITLE: Type Definitions for Keyframe Animation in React Native Reanimated
DESCRIPTION: This snippet provides TypeScript type definitions for the Keyframe class and its constructor arguments. It defines types for the first frame, last frame, and valid keyframe properties, as well as methods for duration, delay, reduceMotion, and callback.
SOURCE: https://github.com/software-mansion/react-native-reanimated/blob/main/packages/docs-reanimated/docs/layout-animations/keyframe-animations.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
type FirstFrame =
  | {
      0: KeyframeProps & { easing?: never };
      from?: never;
    }
  | {
      0?: never;
      from: KeyframeProps & { easing?: never };
    };

type LastFrame =
  | { 100?: KeyframeProps; to?: never }
  | { 100?: never; to: KeyframeProps };

export type ValidKeyframeProps = FirstFrame &
  LastFrame &
  Record<number, KeyframeProps>;

class Keyframe {
  constructor(definitions: ValidKeyframeProps;
  duration(durationMs: number): Keyframe;
  delay(delayMs: number): Keyframe;
  reduceMotion(reduceMotionV: ReduceMotion): Keyframe;
  withCallback(callback: (finished: boolean) => void): Keyframe;
}
```

