TITLE: Implementing a Custom Animated Event Handler Hook in React Native Reanimated
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows the implementation of a custom hook for handling animated pager scroll events. It uses the low-level useHandler and useEvent APIs from React Native Reanimated to create a worklet-based event handler.
SOURCE: https://github.com/software-mansion/react-native-reanimated/blob/main/packages/docs-reanimated/versioned_docs/version-2.x/fundamentals/custom_events.md#2025-04-16_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function useAnimatedPagerScrollHandler(handlers, dependencies) {
  const { context, doDependenciesDiffer } = useHandler(handlers, dependencies);

  return useEvent(
    (event) => {
      'worklet';
      const { onPageScroll } = handlers;

      if (onPageScroll && event.eventName.endsWith('onPageScroll')) {
        onPageScroll(event, context);
      }
    },
    ['onPageScroll'],
    doDependenciesDiffer
  );
}
```

