TITLE: Scroll Event Handler with Distance Calculation
DESCRIPTION: Implements an onScroll handler that calculates which section is currently most visible by comparing distances from the top of the screen, updating the visibleIndex shared value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/software-mansion/react-native-reanimated/blob/main/packages/docs-reanimated/blog/section-list.md#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
  const onScroll = useAnimatedScrollHandler(
    debounce((event) => {
      'worklet';
      const y = event.contentOffset.y + 100;

      let minDistance = Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER;
      let closestIndex = 0;

      for (let i = 0; i < sections.length; i++) {
        const distance = Math.abs(sectionPositions[i] - y);
        if (distance < minDistance) {
          minDistance = distance;
          closestIndex = i;
        }
      }

      visibleIndex.value = closestIndex;
    }, 16)
  );
```

