TITLE: Cancelling Animations on Mutable Values in React
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to properly cancel animations on mutable values when they are no longer needed, especially for infinite animations. This example uses useMemo to create the mutable value and cancelAnimation in the cleanup function of useEffect.
SOURCE: https://github.com/software-mansion/react-native-reanimated/blob/main/packages/docs-reanimated/versioned_docs/version-3.x/advanced/makeMutable.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function App() {
  const mv = useMemo(() => makeMutable(0), []);

  useEffect(() => {
    mv.value = withRepeat(withSpring(100), -1, true); // creates an infinite animation

    return () => {
      cancelAnimation(mv); // âœ… stops the infinite animation on component unmount
    };
  }, []);
}
```

