TITLE: Incorrect Usage of makeMutable in React Component
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates an incorrect way of using makeMutable directly in a component scope. This creates a new mutable value on each render, causing the state of the previous mutable value to be lost.
SOURCE: https://github.com/software-mansion/react-native-reanimated/blob/main/packages/docs-reanimated/versioned_docs/version-3.x/advanced/makeMutable.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function App() {
  const [counter, setCounter] = useState(0);
  const mv = makeMutable(counter); // ðŸš¨ creates a new mutable value on each render

  useEffect(() => {
    const interval = setInterval(() => {
      setCounter((prev) => prev + 1); // updates the counter stored in the component state
    }, 1000);

    return () => {
      clearInterval(interval);
    };
  }, [mv]);

  useAnimatedReaction(
    () => mv.value,
    (value) => {
      console.log(value); // prints 0, 1, 2, ...
    }
  );
}
```

